LAGOS – The Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) has disclosed that 24 ships laden with petroleum products, food items and other goods are expected to berth between December 17 and 29, 2019.
This was contained in NPA’s publication, `Shipping Position’, copy of which was made available to the journalists in Lagos on Tuesday.
The report indicated that the ships were expected to arrive at the Lagos Port Complex.
According to the NPA, the expected ships contained petrol, containers, general cargo, steel pipes, bulk sugar, and buck wheat.
Meanwhile, it was also disclosed that 23 ships, which had already arrived the ports were waiting to berth with containers and fuel. It was further revealed that 15 other ships were at the ports discharging general cargo, containers, buck wheat, bulk gypsum, petrol, base oil, frozen fish, automobile gasoline and ammonium.